{"session_id":"svc-1778801503297921060","seq":2,"type":"session.end","ts":"2026-05-14T23:50:40.315212005Z","data":{"status":"success","output":"The commit is clean. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n**Root cause:** `score.go` lines 60 and 108 gated the entire policy preference switch and provider-preference bias on `!hasPowerBounds`. When `--min-power` or `--max-power` was set, all policy scoring was skipped — so among in-bounds candidates, scoring fell back to raw base+quota+power bonuses, causing metered opus (higher power) to beat free subscription sonnet (lower power).\n\n**Fix:** Instead of removing the guards entirely (which would let metered providers inheriting a \"local\" cost class from their fiz harness outrank subscription candidates), the fix applies only the **subscription/withinQuota bonus** to in-bounds candidates when power bounds are set. Locality bonuses, cost-class rank penalties, and the local-first provider preference remain gated on `!hasPowerBounds`. The `subscription-first` provider preference is applied to in-bounds candidates via a new `else if` branch.\n\n**Tests added** (all passing, all existing tests still green):\n- `TestScorePolicy_MinPowerDoesNotDisableDefaultPolicy` — AC 1\n- `TestScorePolicy_MinPowerSonnetBeatsOpus_DefaultPolicy` — AC 2  \n- `TestScorePolicy_MaxPowerDoesNotDisableProviderPreference` — AC 3","tokens":{"input":21,"output":66239,"cache_read":2121913,"cache_write":152967,"total":66260},"cost_usd":2.20714015,"duration_ms":1136191,"model":"sonnet","sticky":{"key_present":true,"bonus":0},"utilization":{"observed_at":"0001-01-01T00:00:00Z"},"requested_harness":"claude","resolved_harness":"claude","harness_source":"request_harness","requested_model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","resolved_model":"sonnet","metadata":{"DDX_MODE":"bead_execution","attempt_id":"20260514T233141-852debdf","base_rev":"053b8783c0f4fde4de109b8696ae49bddc0000fa","bead_id":"fizeau-dc3cf359","bundle_path":".ddx/executions/20260514T233141-852debdf","prompt_f